SnmpAdminString.name: SnmpAdminString
SnmpAdminString.description: An octet string containing administrative information, preferably in human-readable form.

InetPortNumber.name: InetPortNumber
InetPortNumber.description: Represents a 16 bit port number of an Internet transport layer protocol. Port numbers are assigned by IANA. A current list of all assignments is available from <http://www.iana.org/>. The value zero is object-specific and must be defined as part of the description of any object that uses this syntax. Examples of the usage of zero might include situations where a port number is unknown, or when the value zero is used as a wildcard in a filter.

IpsecAuthType.name: IpsecAuthType
IpsecAuthType.description: The IpsecAuthType is used to specify the authentication type to be used with a particular peer.

IpsecIdType.name: IpsecIdType
IpsecIdType.description: The IpsecIdType is used to specify the type of identifier for a peer to be used with the ID payload.

IpsecEncType.name: IpsecEncType
IpsecEncType.description: The IpsecEncType is used to specify the encryption algorithm to be used when manual keying is used.

eqlIpsecTable.name: eqlIpsecTable
eqlIpsecTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage IPSec global settings This table contains global IPSec settings.

eqlIpsecEntry.name: eqlIpsecEntry
eqlIpsecEntry.description: An entry (row) containing global IPSec settings.

eqlIpsecInstanceId.name: eqlIpsecInstanceId
eqlIpsecInstanceId.description: This index identifies the IPSec instance. This index should always be 1.

eqlIpsecEnable.name: eqlIpsecEnable
eqlIpsecEnable.description: This specifies if IPSec is enabled or disbaled. True for enabled and False for disabled.

eqlIpsecRowStatus.name: eqlIpsecRowStatus
eqlIpsecRowStatus.description: This object indicates the conceptual status of this row. This object may not be set to active if the requirements of the spdIpHeadFiltType object are not met. In other words, if the associated value columns needed by a particular test have not been set, then attempting to change this row to an active state will result in an inconsistentValue error. See the spdIpHeadFiltType object description for further details.

eqlIpsecPolicyTable.name: eqlIpsecPolicyTable
eqlIpsecPolicyTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage IPSec Policy Table. This table contains a list of filter definitions.

eqlIpsecPolicyEntry.name: eqlIpsecPolicyEntry
eqlIpsecPolicyEntry.description: A definition of a particular filter.

eqlIpsecPolicyInstanceId.name: eqlIpsecPolicyInstanceId
eqlIpsecPolicyInstanceId.description: This index identifies the IPSec policy instance.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterName.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterName
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterName.description: The administrative name for this filter.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterIPVersion.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterIPVersion
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterIPVersion.description: The Internet Protocol version the addresses are to match against. The value of this property determines the size and format of the eqlIpsecPolicyFilterAddress and eqlIpsecPolicyFilterLocalAddress.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterAddress.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterAddress
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterAddress.description: The starting address of a source address range that the packet must match against for this filter to be considered TRUE. This object is only used if sourceAddress is set in spdIpHeadFiltType.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterNetmaskLen.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterNetmaskLen
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterNetmaskLen.description: The ending address of a source address range to check a packet against, where the starting is specified by the spdIpHeadFiltSrcAddressBegin object. Set this column to the same value as the spdIpHeadFiltSrcAddressBegin column to get an exact single address match. This object is only used if sourceAddress is set in spdIpHeadFiltType.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterLocalAddress.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterLocalAddress
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterLocalAddress.description: The Local IP Address on the array to bind a policy to. This option is only used when the Peer is of type manual. Can be either a IPv4 or IPV6 address.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterPort.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterPort
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterPort.description: The low port of the port range a packet's source must match against. To match, the port number must be greater than or equal to this value. This object is only used if sourcePort is set in spdIpHeadFiltType. The value of 0 for this object is illegal.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterLocalPort.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterLocalPort
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterLocalPort.description: The low port of the port range a packet's source must match against. To match, the port number must be greater than or equal to this value. This object is only used if sourcePort is set in spdIpHeadFiltType. The value of 0 for this object is illegal. This object specifies the local port to be used.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterProtocol.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterProtocol
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterProtocol.description: The protocol number the incoming packet must match against for this filter to be evaluated as true. This object is only used if protocol is set in spdIpHeadFiltType.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterPeerName.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterPeerName
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterPeerName.description: This specifies the name of the peer this policy must be associated with.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterAction.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterAction
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterAction.description: The action to be taken on packets matching this rule.

eqlIpsecPolicyFilterRowStatus.name: eqlIpsecPolicyFilterRowStatus
eqlIpsecPolicyFilterRowStatus.description: This object indicates the conceptual status of this row. This object may not be set to active if the requirements of the spdIpHeadFiltType object are not met. In other words, if the associated value columns needed by a particular test have not been set, then attempting to change this row to an active state will result in an inconsistentValue error. See the spdIpHeadFiltType object description for further details.

eqlIpsecCertConfigTable.name: eqlIpsecCertConfigTable
eqlIpsecCertConfigTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic IPSec certificate configuration Table. This table contains the list of certificates configured.

eqlIpsecCertConfigEntry.name: eqlIpsecCertConfigEntry
eqlIpsecCertConfigEntry.description: A definition of a particular certificate.

eqlIpsecCertInstanceId.name: eqlIpsecCertInstanceId
eqlIpsecCertInstanceId.description: This index identifies the IPSec certificate instance.

eqlIpsecCertName.name: eqlIpsecCertName
eqlIpsecCertName.description: The administrative name for this certificate.

eqlIpsecCertType.name: eqlIpsecCertType
eqlIpsecCertType.description: The certificate type. Local cert, Root CA cert or intermediate cert.

eqlIpsecCertPassword.name: eqlIpsecCertPassword
eqlIpsecCertPassword.description: The password to use for decrypting certificate.

eqlIpsecCertRowStatus.name: eqlIpsecCertRowStatus
eqlIpsecCertRowStatus.description: This object indicates the conceptual status of this row. This object may not be set to active if the requirements of the spdIpHeadFiltType object are not met. In other words, if the associated value columns needed by a particular test have not been set, then attempting to change this row to an active state will result in an inconsistentValue error. See the spdIpHeadFiltType object description for further details.

eqlIpsecPeerTable.name: eqlIpsecPeerTable
eqlIpsecPeerTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage IPSec peer Table. This table contains the list of peers configured.

eqlIpsecPeerEntry.name: eqlIpsecPeerEntry
eqlIpsecPeerEntry.description: A definition of a particular certificate.

eqlIpsecPeerInstanceId.name: eqlIpsecPeerInstanceId
eqlIpsecPeerInstanceId.description: This index identifies the IPSec policy instance.

eqlIpsecPeerName.name: eqlIpsecPeerName
eqlIpsecPeerName.description: The administrative name for this peer.

eqlIpsecPeerAuthType.name: eqlIpsecPeerAuthType
eqlIpsecPeerAuthType.description: The authentication method used with this peer. Pre-shared keys, certificates and manual keys are the options.

eqlIpsecPeerPreSharedKey.name: eqlIpsecPeerPreSharedKey
eqlIpsecPeerPreSharedKey.description: The pre-shared key to be used during authentication. It is mandatory that this only contain printable ASCII ASCII characters, meaning each byte must be in the range of 33 to 126.

eqlIpsecPeerCertIdType.name: eqlIpsecPeerCertIdType
eqlIpsecPeerCertIdType.description: The identifier type to be used in ID payload. Only applicable if the auth type is certificates.

eqlIpsecPeerCertIdValue.name: eqlIpsecPeerCertIdValue
eqlIpsecPeerCertIdValue.description: The pre-shared key to be used during authentication. Only applicable if the auth type is certificates.

eqlIpsecPeerNullEnc.name: eqlIpsecPeerNullEnc
eqlIpsecPeerNullEnc.description: This specifies if null encryption is to be used. Only applicable if the auth type is certificates or pre-shared keys.

eqlIpsecPeerTunnelMode.name: eqlIpsecPeerTunnelMode
eqlIpsecPeerTunnelMode.description: This specifies if tunnel mode is to be used with this peer.

eqlIpsecPeerTunnelAddressIPVersion.name: eqlIpsecPeerTunnelAddressIPVersion
eqlIpsecPeerTunnelAddressIPVersion.description: The Internet Protocol version the addresses are to match against. The value of this property determines the size and format of the spdIpHeadFiltSrcAddressBegin, spdIpHeadFiltSrcAddressEnd, spdIpHeadFiltDstAddressBegin, and spdIpHeadFiltDstAddressEnd objects. Values of unknown, ipv4z, ipv6z and dns are not legal values for this object.

eqlIpsecPeerTunnelAddress.name: eqlIpsecPeerTunnelAddress
eqlIpsecPeerTunnelAddress.description: The address of the tunnel remote end This object is only used if tunnelMode is set to True.

eqlIpsecPeerIkeV2.name: eqlIpsecPeerIkeV2
eqlIpsecPeerIkeV2.description: This specifies the IKE version to be used with this peer. If the peer talks the other version, the IPSec session will not be established.

eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyEncAlg.name: eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyEncAlg
eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyEncAlg.description: The encryption algorithm to be used. Only applicable if the auth type is manual keys.

eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyEncKeyOut.name: eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyEncKeyOut
eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyEncKeyOut.description: The encryption key to be used in the outbound direction. Specified as a hex string. Only applicable if the auth type is manual keys.

eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyEncKeyIn.name: eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyEncKeyIn
eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyEncKeyIn.description: The encryption key to be used in the inbound direction. Specified as a hex string. Only applicable if the auth type is manual keys.

eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyAuthAlg.name: eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyAuthAlg
eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyAuthAlg.description: The authentication algorithm to be used. Only applicable if the auth type is manual keys.

eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyAuthKeyOut.name: eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyAuthKeyOut
eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyAuthKeyOut.description: The authentication key to be used in the outbound direction. Specified as a string. Only applicable if the auth type is manual keys.

eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyAuthKeyIn.name: eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyAuthKeyIn
eqlIpsecPeerManualKeyAuthKeyIn.description: The authentication key to be used in the inbound direction. Specified as a string. Only applicable if the auth type is manual keys.

eqlIpsecPeerManualKeySpiOut.name: eqlIpsecPeerManualKeySpiOut
eqlIpsecPeerManualKeySpiOut.description: The SPI to be used in the outbound direction. Only applicable if the auth type is manual keys.

eqlIpsecPeerManualKeySpiIn.name: eqlIpsecPeerManualKeySpiIn
eqlIpsecPeerManualKeySpiIn.description: The SPI to be used in the inbound direction. Only applicable if the auth type is manual keys.

eqlIpsecPeerRowStatus.name: eqlIpsecPeerRowStatus
eqlIpsecPeerRowStatus.description: This object indicates the conceptual status of this row. This object may not be set to active if the requirements of the spdIpHeadFiltType object are not met. In other words, if the associated value columns needed by a particular test have not been set, then attempting to change this row to an active state will result in an inconsistentValue error. See the spdIpHeadFiltType object description for further details.

eqlIpsecCertDisplayTable.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplayTable
eqlIpsecCertDisplayTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic IPSec certificate display Table. This table is used to display certificate details.

eqlIpsecCertDisplayEntry.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplayEntry
eqlIpsecCertDisplayEntry.description: Contents of a particular certificate instance for display.

eqlIpsecCertDisplayName.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplayName
eqlIpsecCertDisplayName.description: The administrative name for this certificate.

eqlIpsecCertDisplayIssuedToDName.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplayIssuedToDName
eqlIpsecCertDisplayIssuedToDName.description: Display string for the field issued to distinguished name.

eqlIpsecCertDisplaySerialNumber.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplaySerialNumber
eqlIpsecCertDisplaySerialNumber.description: Display string for the field serial number.

eqlIpsecCertDisplayIssuedByDName.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplayIssuedByDName
eqlIpsecCertDisplayIssuedByDName.description: Display string for the field issued by distinguished name.

eqlIpsecCertDisplayIssuedOn.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplayIssuedOn
eqlIpsecCertDisplayIssuedOn.description: Display string for the field issued on.

eqlIpsecCertDisplayExpiresOn.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplayExpiresOn
eqlIpsecCertDisplayExpiresOn.description: Display string for the field expires on.

eqlIpsecCertDisplaySha1Fingerprint.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplaySha1Fingerprint
eqlIpsecCertDisplaySha1Fingerprint.description: Display string for the field SHA1 finger print.

eqlIpsecCertDisplayMd5Fingerprint.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplayMd5Fingerprint
eqlIpsecCertDisplayMd5Fingerprint.description: Display string for the field MD5 finger print.

eqlIpsecCertDisplayLocal.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplayLocal
eqlIpsecCertDisplayLocal.description: Boolean that indicates if this is a localm certificate or not.

eqlIpsecCertDisplayFormat.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplayFormat
eqlIpsecCertDisplayFormat.description: The certificate format. x.509 or pkcs12.

eqlIpsecCertDisplaySubAltName.name: eqlIpsecCertDisplaySubAltName
eqlIpsecCertDisplaySubAltName.description: Display string for the field MD5 finger print.

eqlIpsecSecAssocTable.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocTable
eqlIpsecSecAssocTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic IPSec security association Table. This table is used to display the security association details.

eqlIpsecSecAssocEntry.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocEntry
eqlIpsecSecAssocEntry.description: Contents of a particular SA instance for display.

eqlIpsecSecAssocInstanceIdHigh.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocInstanceIdHigh
eqlIpsecSecAssocInstanceIdHigh.description: This index carries the high-order 32-bit of the instance ID that identifies the IPSec security association.

eqlIpsecSecAssocInstanceIdLow.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocInstanceIdLow
eqlIpsecSecAssocInstanceIdLow.description: This index carries the low-order 32-bit of the instance ID that identifies the IPSec security association.

eqlIpsecSecAssocSrcAddressIPVersion.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocSrcAddressIPVersion
eqlIpsecSecAssocSrcAddressIPVersion.description: The IP version of the source endpoint.

eqlIpsecSecAssocSrcAddress.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocSrcAddress
eqlIpsecSecAssocSrcAddress.description: The IP address of the source endpoint.

eqlIpsecSecAssocDstAddressIPVersion.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocDstAddressIPVersion
eqlIpsecSecAssocDstAddressIPVersion.description: The IP version of the destination endpoint.

eqlIpsecSecAssocDstAddress.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocDstAddress
eqlIpsecSecAssocDstAddress.description: The IP address of the destination endpoint.

eqlIpsecSecAssocSpi.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocSpi
eqlIpsecSecAssocSpi.description: SPI used in the security association.

eqlIpsecSecAssocEncKey.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocEncKey
eqlIpsecSecAssocEncKey.description: Display string for the encryption key used in the SA.

eqlIpsecSecAssocAuthKey.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocAuthKey
eqlIpsecSecAssocAuthKey.description: Display string for the authentication key used in the SA.

eqlIpsecSecAssocManual.name: eqlIpsecSecAssocManual
eqlIpsecSecAssocManual.description: True means SA is from a manual key configured.

eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteTable.name: eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteTable
eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic IPSec stale security association delete Table. This table is used to indicate the destination address and type of all security associations to delete.

eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteEntry.name: eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteEntry
eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteEntry.description: Contents of a particular SA instance for delete.

eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteInstanceId.name: eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteInstanceId
eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteInstanceId.description: This index identifies the IPSec stale SA delete instance.

eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteDestAddressIP.name: eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteDestAddressIPVersion
eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteDestAddressIP.description: The IP version of the destination address of the security associations to delete.

eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteDestAddress.name: eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteDestAddress
eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteDestAddress.description: The destination address of the security associations to delete.

eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteRowStatus.name: eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteRowStatus
eqlIpsecStaleSecAssocDeleteRowStatus.description: This object indicates the conceptual status of this row.
